<div class="mb-16">
  <%= render "railsui/shared/sticky_subhead", title: "Dropdowns", subtitle: "With dividers" %>

  <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-full mb-10">
    <p>Divide items in a list using a <%= code "divide-y" %> class from Tailwind CSS.</p>

    <p>Depending on how your dropdown list data originates, you may need to get creative on assigning padding between the first and last items in the dropdown menu. </p>

    <p>By default each item has a padding offset of <%= code "py-1" %> applied. You may find that you will need to override this for the first and last items to produce an even gap across all menu list items while displaying dividers.</p>
  </div>

<div data-controller="dropdown" class="relative inline-block">
  <button type="button" data-action="click->dropdown#toggle click@window->dropdown#hide" class="btn btn-white pr-3">
    Dropdown with dividers
    <%= icon "chevron-down", styles: "w-3 h-3 ml-2" %>
  </button>
  <ul
    class="hidden transition transform origin-to-right absolute -left-1 top-10 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-xl shadow-slate-900/10 border border-slate-200 min-w-[180px] z-50 py-1 text-[15px] divide-y"
    data-dropdown-target="menu"
    data-transition-enter-from="opacity-0 scale-95"
    data-transition-enter-to="opacity-100 scale-100"
    data-transition-leave-from="opacity-100 scale-100"
    data-transition-leave-to="opacity-0 scale-95"
    >
    <li class="py-1 first-of-type:pt-0">
      <a href="#" class="px-4 py-[.4rem] hover:text-indigo-600 block">Edit</a>
    <li class="py-1">
      <a href="#" class="px-4 py-[.4rem] hover:text-indigo-600 block">Share</a>
      <a href="#" class="px-4 py-[.4rem] hover:text-indigo-600 block">Export</a>
    </li>
    <li class="py-1 last-of-type:pb-0">
      <a href="#" class="px-4 py-[.4rem] hover:text-indigo-600 block">Delete</a>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>


